OL,7,FSale pleaded guilty to a second charge
OL,8,Fof causing death while uninsured. The
OL,9,Fjudge ordered the count to lie on
OL,10,Ffile, but Mr Bruce said it would be
OL,11,Fpart of the prosecution case that Sale
OL,12,Fwas uninsured at the time of the
OL,13,Fcollision
OL,15,FDefending, David James said: "It is a
OL,16,Ffact there was an absence of
OL,17,Finsurance. I will be able to explain
OL,18,Fwhy that happened in the
OL,19,Fcircumstances."
